
These are single point and force calculations of 3D periodic (MgO)_4 
with different lattice parameter A. I used HF/DIIS/Tight with 
the MgO_C98-SPLIT.bas. These are parallel calculations, but 
the problem remains with serial.
 
The error:
The zero lattice gradient does not correspond the minimum
of the energy. I could see that only for 3D-periodic systems and
I got also the same thing for a 2x2x2 supercell.
=======================================================
(MgO)_4 tight,crystal basis set
  A           E           dE/dA
4.150 -1098.41440285 -0.0555793407
4.250 -1098.44874370 -0.0263157353
4.300 -1098.45757865 -0.0125683742
4.350 -1098.46156232  0.0005221943
4.375 -1098.46188081  0.0068133229 <<< min(E)
4.400 -1098.46115515  0.0129289292
4.450 -1098.45676869  0.0246320509
=======================================================
 
Setting:
